<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <title>Blog | Idempotent</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="css/blog.css" />
    <!-- Link to your CSS file -->
    <link
      rel="stylesheet"
      href="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/font-awesome/6.0.0-beta3/css/all.min.css"
      integrity="sha384-k6RqeWeci5ZR/Lv4MR0sA0FfDOMf6KZ6iA3eRVg8FmYp5/0cU0m6beL84G0iX6R"
      crossorigin="anonymous"
    />
    <link
      rel="stylesheet"
      href="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/font-awesome/6.6.0/css/all.min.css"
    />
  </head>
  <body>
    <header>
      <nav class="navbar">
        <div class="logo">
          <a href="#">Idempotent <i class="fa-solid fa-arrow-turn-down"></i></a>
        </div>
        <div class="menu-icon" onclick="toggleMenu()">
          <i class="fas fa-bars"></i>
        </div>
        <ul class="menu">
          <li><a href="/Home">Home</a></li>
          <li><a href="/Services">Services</a></li>
          <li><a href="/Projects">Projects</a></li>
          <li><a href="/Blog" class="active">Blog</a></li>
          <li><a href="/Contact">Contact</a></li>
          <li><a href="/Community">Community</a></li>
          <% if (session.userId) { %>

          <li>
            <a href="/Profile" class="active"
              >Hello <%= session.userName %>!
            </a>
          </li>
          <% }else {%>
          <li><a href="/Login">Login</a></li>
          <% } %>
        </ul>
      </nav>
    </header>

    <main>
      <section class="blog-header">
        <h1>Welcome to Our Blog</h1>
        <p>
          Stay updated with the latest insights and trends in the tech world.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="blog-container">
        <div class="posts">
          <article class="post-card">
            <img src="../images/async.png" alt="Post Image 1" />
            <div class="post-content">
              <h2><a href="#">Understanding Asynchronous JavaScript</a></h2>
              <p class="post-meta">
                Posted on October 15, 2024 by <span>Admin</span>
              </p>
              <p class="excerpt">
                Explore the asynchronous nature of JavaScript, covering
                promises, async/await, and how to manage asynchronous code
                effectively.
              </p>
              <p class="full-content" style="display: none">
                This full content dives deep into asynchronous JavaScript,
                exploring callback functions, promises, and async/await. We'll
                go over how each of these approaches handles asynchronous code,
                common use cases, and how you can integrate them effectively in
                various scenarios to improve your app’s responsiveness.
              </p>
              <a href="#" class="read-more" onclick="showMore(this)"
                >Read More</a
              >
            </div>
          </article>

          <article class="post-card">
            <img src="../images/starting_flask.png" alt="Post Image 2" />
            <div class="post-content">
              <h2><a href="#">Building RESTful APIs with Python</a></h2>
              <p class="post-meta">
                Posted on October 10, 2024 by <span>Admin</span>
              </p>
              <p>
                Learn how to create RESTful APIs using Flask and Django. We'll
                cover best practices and common pitfalls.
              </p>

              <a href="#" class="read-more">Read More</a>
            </div>
          </article>

          <article class="post-card">
            <img
              src="../images/how-to-learn-react-js-quickly.jpeg"
              alt="Post Image 3"
            />
            <div class="post-content">
              <h2><a href="#">A Beginner's Guide to React</a></h2>
              <p class="post-meta">
                Posted on October 5, 2024 by <span>Admin</span>
              </p>
              <p>
                Dive into the world of React, learning about components, state,
                props, and how to build dynamic web applications.
              </p>
              <a href="#" class="read-more">Read More</a>
            </div>
          </article>

          <article class="post-card">
            <img src="../images/grids.jpg" alt="Post Image 4" />
            <div class="post-content">
              <h2><a href="#">CSS Grid vs Flexbox: When to Use What</a></h2>
              <p class="post-meta">
                Posted on September 28, 2024 by <span>Admin</span>
              </p>
              <p>
                Understand the differences between CSS Grid and Flexbox, and
                learn how to choose the right layout method for your design.
              </p>
              <a href="#" class="read-more">Read More</a>
            </div>
          </article>

          <article class="post-card">
            <img src="../images/Git-Tips-1-1024x524.png" alt="Post Image 5" />
            <div class="post-content">
              <h2><a href="#">Mastering Git: Tips and Tricks</a></h2>
              <p class="post-meta">
                Posted on September 20, 2024 by <span>Admin</span>
              </p>
              <p>
                Git is a powerful tool for version control. Discover tips and
                tricks that can enhance your workflow and make collaboration
                easier.
              </p>
              <a href="#" class="read-more">Read More</a>
            </div>
          </article>
        </div>

        <aside class="sidebar">
          <h3>Categories</h3>
          <ul>
            <li><a href="#">JavaScript</a></li>
            <li><a href="#">Python</a></li>
            <li><a href="#">React</a></li>
            <li><a href="#">CSS</a></li>
            <li><a href="#">Git</a></li>
          </ul>

          <h3>Recent Posts</h3>
          <ul>
            <li><a href="#">Understanding Asynchronous JavaScript</a></li>
            <li><a href="#">Building RESTful APIs with Python</a></li>
            <li><a href="#">A Beginner's Guide to React</a></li>
            <li><a href="#">CSS Grid vs Flexbox: When to Use What</a></li>
            <li><a href="#">Mastering Git: Tips and Tricks</a></li>
          </ul>

          <h3>Follow Us</h3>
          <div class="social-links">
            <a href="#"><i class="fab fa-twitter"></i></a>
            <a href="#"><i class="fab fa-facebook-f"></i></a>
            <a href="#"><i class="fab fa-instagram"></i></a>
            <a href="#"><i class="fab fa-linkedin-in"></i></a>
          </div>
        </aside>
      </section>
    </main>

    <footer>
      <p>&copy; 2024 Idempotent. All rights reserved.</p>
    </footer>

    <script>
      function toggleMenu() {
        const menu = document.querySelector(".menu");
        menu.classList.toggle("active");
      }
      function showMore(button) {
        const postContent = button.previousElementSibling;
        const excerpt = postContent.previousElementSibling;

        if (postContent.style.display === "none") {
          postContent.style.display = "block";
          excerpt.style.display = "none";
          button.textContent = "Show Less";
        } else {
          postContent.style.display = "none";
          excerpt.style.display = "block";
          button.textContent = "Read More";
        }
      }
    </script>
  </body>
</html>
